Package tech.tablesaw.selection

Interface Selection

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Filter, it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.ints.IntIterable, Iterable<Integer>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BitmapBackedSelection

    public interface Selection
extends it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.ints.IntIterable, Filter
    A selection maintains an ordered set of ints that can be used to eval rows from a table or column

      • get

        int get​(int i)
        Returns the value of the ith element. For example, if there are three ints {4, 32, 71} in the selection, get(0) returns 4, get(1) returns 32, and get(2) returns 71 It can be useful if you need to iterate over the data, although there is also an iterator
